1. Open Python Interactive Mode

In the terminal, type:

python3


You will see the interactive prompt: >>>.

2. Import the library
>>> from urllib.request import urlopen

3. Open a website
>>> site = urlopen("http://example.com")

4. Read the page content
>>> print(site.read())  # reads the full content

5. Check the HTTP response code
>>> print(site.getcode())  # returns 200, 404, etc.

6. Get the accessed URL
>>> print(site.geturl())

7. View HTTP headers
>>> print(site.info())  # shows all headers

8. Check the web server
>>> head = site.info()
>>> print(head['Server'])

9. Exit interactive mode
>>> exit()

